Content:
No it isn't.
Following up on your post, which is btw, great, I'd add Mission Control also breaks my use of Expos.<p>On Snow Leopard, most of the time, I used only one space and, as I've been using it on a 13.3" MBP, my windows were always using most of the screen and I usually have more than one window of a given app open at the same time (Finder or Text Wrangler for example).<p>To see multiple app windows, my workflow was:
1. Swipe four fingers down (gesture for Expos);
2. Select any window of any given app.<p>Now, I must use Mission Control:
1. Gesture for Mission Control;
2. Select the app;
3. Gesture for Expos;
4. Select my window.<p>What used to take 2 steps, takes four.
